title: iPS cell line Clone 1 No Dox Replicate 1
source_name_ch1: iPS cell line Clone 1 No Dox Replicate 1
characteristics_ch1: cell type: induced pluripotent stem cells
treatment_protocol_ch1: - or + doxycycline (500 ng/ml); 6 days for iPS cells and 14 days for iPS-derived endothelial cells
growth_protocol_ch1: iPS cells were grown in feeder free conditions on vitronectin coated plates and cultured in Essential E8 medium (Invitrogen).
growth_protocol_ch1.1: iPS cells were grown in feeder free conditions on vitronectin coated plates and cultured in Essential E8 medium (Invitrogen). Differentiation of iPS cells into endothelial cells were adapted from Lian et al. (2014) and Patsch et al. (2015). Cells were treated with 8 uM CHIR99021 (Tocris Bioscience) for on day 0 and day 1, and 2 uM CHIR99021 on day 2-4. Day 5, cells were collected for CD34+ were selected using the CD34 MicroBead Kit (Miltenyi Biotec). Purified CD34 cells were cultured on collagen coated plates with EGM-2 media (Lonza) supplemented with 25 ng/ml VEGF165 (PEPROTECH).
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA samples were extracted using Trizol Reagent (ThermoFisher) adapted from the manufacturer’s instructions, using 100% ethanol in place of isopropanol. Precipitated RNA was resuspended in RNase- and DNase-free water and DNA digestion was performed using DNase I (Roche) with 2U/ul of RNasin Plus (Promega) for 1 hr at room temperature. RNeasy Mini Kit was used for RNA purification and DNase I removal following the RNA Cleanup protocol from the manufacturer’s instructions.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: The NEBNext Ultra™ II Directional RNA Library Prep Kit for Illumina, NEBNext Poly(A) mRNA Magnetic Isolation Module, and NEBNext Multiplex Oligos for Illumina were used to prepare sequencing libraries following the manufacturer’s instructions (New England Biolabs, Inc). All libraries were prepared with 1 ug of starting RNA.
data_processing: For all samples, FastQC was used to evaluate quality of data.
data_processing.1: Libraries were aligned to genome build GRch38 using HISAT2 (Kim et al., 2015, 2019)
data_processing.2: Mapped reads were quantified using featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014).
data_processing.3: Differential expression analysis was conducted by using the R package edgeR (McCarthy et al. 2012)
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab delimited files containg differentially expressed genes generated by edgeR within R (McCarthy et al., 2012)
cell type:ch1: induced pluripotent stem cells

growth_protocol_ch1.1: iPS cells were grown in feeder free conditions on vitronectin coated plates and cultured in Essential E8 medium (Invitrogen). Differentiation of iPS cells into endothelial cells were adapted from Lian et al. (2014) and Patsch et al. (2015). Cells were treated with 8 uM CHIR99021 (Tocris Bioscience) for on day 0 and day 1, and 2 uM CHIR99021 on day 2-4. Day 5, cells were collected for CD34+ were selected using the CD34 MicroBead Kit (Miltenyi Biotec). Purified CD34 cells were cultured on collagen coated plates with EGM-2 media (Lonza) supplemented with 25 ng/ml VEGF165 (PEPROTECH).
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA samples were extracted using Trizol Reagent (ThermoFisher) adapted from the manufacturer’s instructions, using 100% ethanol in place of isopropanol. Precipitated RNA was resuspended in RNase- and DNase-free water and DNA digestion was performed using DNase I (Roche) with 2U/ul of RNasin Plus (Promega) for 1 hr at room temperature. RNeasy Mini Kit was used for RNA purification and DNase I removal following the RNA Cleanup protocol from the manufacturer’s instructions.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: The NEBNext Ultra™ II Directional RNA Library Prep Kit for Illumina, NEBNext Poly(A) mRNA Magnetic Isolation Module, and NEBNext Multiplex Oligos for Illumina were used to prepare sequencing libraries following the manufacturer’s instructions (New England Biolabs, Inc). All libraries were prepared with 1 ug of starting RNA.
data_processing: For all samples, FastQC was used to evaluate quality of data.
data_processing.1: Libraries were aligned to genome build GRch38 using HISAT2 (Kim et al., 2015, 2019)
data_processing.2: Mapped reads were quantified using featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014).
data_processing.3: Differential expression analysis was conducted by using the R package edgeR (McCarthy et al. 2012)
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab delimited files containg differentially expressed genes generated by edgeR within R (McCarthy et al., 2012)

growth_protocol_ch1.1: iPS cells were grown in feeder free conditions on vitronectin coated plates and cultured in Essential E8 medium (Invitrogen). Differentiation of iPS cells into endothelial cells were adapted from Lian et al. (2014) and Patsch et al. (2015). Cells were treated with 8 uM CHIR99021 (Tocris Bioscience) for on day 0 and day 1, and 2 uM CHIR99021 on day 2-4. Day 5, cells were collected for CD34+ were selected using the CD34 MicroBead Kit (Miltenyi Biotec). Purified CD34 cells were cultured on collagen coated plates with EGM-2 media (Lonza) supplemented with 25 ng/ml VEGF165 (PEPROTECH).
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA samples were extracted using Trizol Reagent (ThermoFisher) adapted from the manufacturer’s instructions, using 100% ethanol in place of isopropanol. Precipitated RNA was resuspended in RNase- and DNase-free water and DNA digestion was performed using DNase I (Roche) with 2U/ul of RNasin Plus (Promega) for 1 hr at room temperature. RNeasy Mini Kit was used for RNA purification and DNase I removal following the RNA Cleanup protocol from the manufacturer’s instructions.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: The NEBNext Ultra™ II Directional RNA Library Prep Kit for Illumina, NEBNext Poly(A) mRNA Magnetic Isolation Module, and NEBNext Multiplex Oligos for Illumina were used to prepare sequencing libraries following the manufacturer’s instructions (New England Biolabs, Inc). All libraries were prepared with 1 ug of starting RNA.
data_processing: For all samples, FastQC was used to evaluate quality of data.
data_processing.1: Libraries were aligned to genome build GRch38 using HISAT2 (Kim et al., 2015, 2019)
data_processing.2: Mapped reads were quantified using featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014).
data_processing.3: Differential expression analysis was conducted by using the R package edgeR (McCarthy et al. 2012)
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab delimited files containg differentially expressed genes generated by edgeR within R (McCarthy et al., 2012)

growth_protocol_ch1: Differentiation of iPS cells into endothelial cells were adapted from Lian et al. (2014) and Patsch et al. (2015). Cells were treated with 8 uM CHIR99021 (Tocris Bioscience) for on day 0 and day 1, and 2 uM CHIR99021 on day 2-4. Day 5, cells were collected for CD34+ were selected using the CD34 MicroBead Kit (Miltenyi Biotec). Purified CD34 cells were cultured on collagen coated plates with EGM-2 media (Lonza) supplemented with 25 ng/ml VEGF165 (PEPROTECH).
growth_protocol_ch1.1: iPS cells were grown in feeder free conditions on vitronectin coated plates and cultured in Essential E8 medium (Invitrogen). Differentiation of iPS cells into endothelial cells were adapted from Lian et al. (2014) and Patsch et al. (2015). Cells were treated with 8 uM CHIR99021 (Tocris Bioscience) for on day 0 and day 1, and 2 uM CHIR99021 on day 2-4. Day 5, cells were collected for CD34+ were selected using the CD34 MicroBead Kit (Miltenyi Biotec). Purified CD34 cells were cultured on collagen coated plates with EGM-2 media (Lonza) supplemented with 25 ng/ml VEGF165 (PEPROTECH).
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA samples were extracted using Trizol Reagent (ThermoFisher) adapted from the manufacturer’s instructions, using 100% ethanol in place of isopropanol. Precipitated RNA was resuspended in RNase- and DNase-free water and DNA digestion was performed using DNase I (Roche) with 2U/ul of RNasin Plus (Promega) for 1 hr at room temperature. RNeasy Mini Kit was used for RNA purification and DNase I removal following the RNA Cleanup protocol from the manufacturer’s instructions.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: The NEBNext Ultra™ II Directional RNA Library Prep Kit for Illumina, NEBNext Poly(A) mRNA Magnetic Isolation Module, and NEBNext Multiplex Oligos for Illumina were used to prepare sequencing libraries following the manufacturer’s instructions (New England Biolabs, Inc). All libraries were prepared with 1 ug of starting RNA.
data_processing: For all samples, FastQC was used to evaluate quality of data.
data_processing.1: Libraries were aligned to genome build GRch38 using HISAT2 (Kim et al., 2015, 2019)
data_processing.2: Mapped reads were quantified using featureCounts (Liao et al., 2014).
data_processing.3: Differential expression analysis was conducted by using the R package edgeR (McCarthy et al. 2012)
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab delimited files containg differentially expressed genes generated by edgeR within R (McCarthy et al., 2012)
cell type:ch1: iPS cell line derived Endothelial Cells
